item.description:
League of Legends - Summoner Showcase #24
Play League of Legends FREE at http://signup.leagueoflegends.com/?ref=ss24 Summoners! Give your eyes a rest from all those games and check out this new Summoner Showcase! My LoLing Ponies http://www.leagueoflegends.com/board/showthread.php?t=614685 Footman is no stranger to community contests, and this time he's asked summoners to draw My Little Pony versions of champions. It is more entertaining and creative than you could ever imagine. League Origami http://www.flickr.com/photos/tohs_origami/5153051091/ Armorbreak has incredible dexterity and skill, and utilizes both to fold plain, uninteresting paper into friggin' awesome champion figures! We've rarely seen Blitzcrank and Cho'Gath look so delicate. Dance Master Phreak http://theuglydance.com/?v=zbbqhnddfz You can now control Phreak's smooth dance moves! We were the last to know about UglyDance where you upload a photograph and make a figure dance around, but luckily we were introduced under the best possible circumstances. Next we expect a flash app: Phreak's Mad Game. Make it happen, summoners! We've wrapped up one more week of inventive fan work, but keep your eyes open for more submissions to send in to Summoner_Showcase@RiotGames.com! We look at each one and Keep them in a vault for release every Friday. Fold some paper, practice your favorite Phreak dance, and we'll see you next week!

item.title: RIP AJ Perez - Tribute to Young Actor & Performer, Died at 18 [1993-2011]
item.description:
RIP AJ Perez - Tribute to Young Actor & Performer, Died at 18 [1993-2011]
Read the whole story in my blog, http://www.bluemoonray.com/2011/04/rip-aj-perez-died-from-vehicular.html like his father's statements, correction from this tribute video, etc (This is a tribute video I made for AJ Perez, I used to tweet with him in twitter, watched his performances in ASAP every sunday. One of the videos I made, wherein I'm totally sad while making it... It's for you Aj...) Antonello Joseph Sarte Perez (born February 17, 1993) is a Filipino actor, a member of ABS-CBN's circle of homegrown talents collectively known as Star Magic, a performer in ASAP Sunday Variety Show died at the age of 18, due to a vehicular accident in Panici, Tarlac. While heading back to Manila from an event in Dagupan (Bangus Festival), A truck bumped at the side part of the van he was riding, where AJ's head was leaning. He was brought to Paniqui, Tarlac Clinic, dead already. Currently, AJ is one of the lead actors in Hit TV Show "Sabel" and a regular performer in ASAP, also a member of a teen male group "Gigger Boys". May your soul rest in peace and you will always be remembered, AJ... Condolences to AJ's family, friends and relatives. :( I'll miss him in twitter & in ASAP every sunday. I dunno what's with number 17: he was born in Feb17, Died at April17, his jersey no. is 17, his twitter account is @ajperez17 . His last tweet in twitter: "On the way home already from Dagupan.Long drive ahead.. Thanks to everybody who watched, thanks to zui for the gifts.And hi again to jarred!". He also believes in the saying "I'll take character over reputation. Your character is what you really are, while your reputation is merely what others think you are. ". He was also in Boracay on the first week of April2011, also a photo of AJ Perez with Rico Yan in ABS-CBN Hallway (See photos in http://www.bluemoonray.com/2011/04/rip-aj-perez-died-from-vehicular.html ) AJ Perez' true to life story will be featured in Maalaala Mo Kaya (MMK) on April 30, I hope everyone will watch it. Indeed, life is too short. Cherish every moment while we're still living. God be with you always, AJ... Watch this tribute video I made... :( VISIT http://www.bluemoonray.com/2011/04/rip-aj-perez-died-from-vehicular.html for other news & updates about AJ PEREZ' death. :((
